In a cohort of 77 patients with an MDD diagnosis of HP, 53 (69%) patients underwent BAL (14 with nonfibrotic HP, 39 with fibrotic HP).119 The median BAL lymphocyte count was higher in nonfibrotic HP (46%; range, 20%-80%) compared to fibrotic HP (19%; range, 11%-41%). No difference was observed in the proportion of nonfibrotic HP and fibrotic HP subjects with a BAL lymphocyte percentage cutoff of > 20%, > 30%, or > 40%.

Remarks: BAL fluid analysis can narrow the differential diagnosis by excluding competing causes, particularly in nonfibrotic HP (eg, infection). However, in patients with a high pretest probability of HP, the BAL cellular analysis may not significantly alter the diagnostic approach.

